Use APC cache for Docker and fix bug with changing component sort orderBy default, the file cache is used, but this breaks the throttling detection when authenticating.nThe APC cache is tagged and will allow you to log in again after installation.n---nWhen changing the sort order, a form with hidden inputs for every component was serialized. The hidden inputsnhad names in the form of `component[id]`. When you removed components, there would be holes in this ID sequence,nyielding a serialized array with empty values (since JS arrays always have every index until the highest one, evennif you don't specify a value).nnThis is fixed by just passing an array of component IDs in the desired sort order to the API endpoint. The APInwill then update the components based on the implicit given sort order. Much simpler.n

Display the metric's suffix in tooltip.When we mouseovered on a point on a metric, the value was shown but thensuffix wasn't.nIt was due to a curly bracket issue, the tooltip option wasn't givennas an option sub-object, but as a third argument of the Chartnconstructor. A curly bracket was closed to early.nThis is fixed and the suffix is now displayed.nnRelated to CachetHQ/Cachet#2848n

Prevents to select metric points in future.The metrics had problem with the points, if I post/save a metric pointnthat is created in the future, it was selected.nnExample:nIt is 10:00 am, I post or save a metric point and it's 'created at'n10:30 am. Using the Last 12 hours the metric point would be selected.nnThis update is applied on all the SQL queries, on minutes, hours, days.nnRelated to CachetHQ/Cachet#2848n

Improves sorting of metric's labels.When selecting the time of metric's points only the time was selected,nnot the date. The issue with this is mainly in the view Last 12 hours.nExample:nIt's 11:10 am and I choose the Last 12 hours view, the metrics pointsnwill be from 23:00 yesterday to 11:00 am today.nWhen giving all these datas and labels to ChartJS, it sorts the pointsnby label from lower to highter. It means 23:00 (from yesterday) will benafter the datas of today, it doesn't have sense.nnTo fix it, I've added in the repositories the date in addition to thentime. So it's no longer 11:00 that is selected but 2018-01-15 11:00.nI've updated the Metric vue in order to cut the label when displaying sonit doesn't change the displaying.nBecause there are metric views that are based on date but not time,nthere is a condition in the Metric vue to cut the string only if thentime is present.nnRelated to CachetHQ/Cachet#2848n

Set the mail username optional in setupDuring the setup process email informations were asked:n  - Drivern  - Hostn  - Usernamen  - PasswordnnIn some situations the username is not useful because the Cachet'snhost may be configured to forward email to a server.nnThe problem is the username was required, so we had to set a usernamenand then update the .env file to remove it.nnTo fix this problem, the mail username has been set to optional innthe setup. So if someone needs a username it still can use this field,nand otherwise people can let it empty.nnSee: #3244n

Let the mail_username required except for sendmailDuring the setup the mail_username was required and it was thennundone, so using the sendmail driver we can let the username empty.nnIt would be bad to let the username optional for every drivers, becausenin some configurations, like SMTP, the username is required for the SMTPnserver so if the user let it empty its mail configuration will be bad.nnThe mail_username is now optional only if the mail driver is sendmail.nnSee: #3244n
